lfiram, Nalmefene, Nicotine, Codeine, Naltrexone, Oxymorphone, Tapentadol, More', 'Moricizine, Tocainide, Bretylium, Mexiletine', 1767369485);
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO drug_interactions (id, ingredient1, ingredient2, severity, effect, source, management_text, mechanism_text, recommendation, risk_level, type, metabolism_info, source_url, reference_text, alternatives_a, alternatives_b, updated_at) VALUES (88145, 'Flibanserin', 'Methadone', 'Moderate', 'The central nervous system (CNS) effects of flibanserin such as somnolence and fatigue may be potentiated by concomitant use of other agents with CNS depressant effects. The risk of CNS depression is increased if flibanserin is taken during waking hours or with alcohol or other CNS depressants.', 'DDInter', 'Patients receiving flibanserin with other agents that can cause CNS depression should be apprised of the potential for increased adverse effects such as drowsiness, dizziness, lightheadedness, and fatigue. Patients should not drive, operate machinery, or engage in hazardous activities requiring mental alertness and motor coordination for at least 6 hours after taking flibanserin.', 'Synergism', 'Patients receiving flibanserin with other agents that can cause CNS depression should be apprised of the potential for increased adverse effects such as drowsiness, dizziness, lightheadedness, and fatigue.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/88246/', '', 'Acamprosate, Lofexidine, Naltrexone, Varenicline, Disulfiram, Nalmefene, Nicotine, Naltrexone, Acetaminophen, Ibuprofen, Celecoxib, More', 'Bremelanotide, Black cohosh, Cabergoline', 1767369485);
